Reference #: 20-2961

Open Date: 11/3/2020

Location: Greenbelt, MD

US Citizenship Required: Yes


Job Description:
Science Systems and Applications, Inc. (SSAI) is seeking a full-time web application developer to join the Earth Science Data Systems Program communications team based at NASA's Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland.

This new position will be part of a growing team responsible for the development, deployment, and maintenance of several websites and web-based applications. Our first project will entail migrating our main website from a proprietary CMS/publishing solution to one that utilizes COTS/open source software and this migration will provide a perfect opportunity to develop new approaches to meeting the information needs of NASA Earth science data users and directing them to the resources that will be most useful.

Other applications under development will utilize existing APIs to feed our data model as well as developing our own APIs to meet the information needs of a distributed data community. We will also explore using our data model to craft knowledge management tools to better serve our stakeholders, scientists, and data users and to develop knowledge workflows that encourage narrative-driven discovery of NASA Earth science data.

The ideal candidate is an experienced web application developer, particularly focused on PHP, who has interests in a wide variety of application development opportunities and is looking to be part of a dynamic team who is experimenting with several different web-based platforms. Some of the work will be part of a larger effort, other work will be smaller, encapsulated efforts, but all is focused on delivering an experience to various audiences that will inform and create awareness about the breadth of data held within NASA’s Earth Science Division.

We offer an exciting work environment, a reasonably flexible schedule, a 40-hour workweek, and competitive benefits and salary. You will get to walk the halls and work with some of the brightest minds in NASA science, and share the fruits of their labor with the whole world. You will also be given opportunities to share your creative ideas and development techniques with our larger NASA community.

** All applicants will be required to submit a code sample or point us to your personal GitHub (or similar). **


Must be U.S. Citizen; position is full-time.


Please note: Due to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, this position will require telecommuting until at least March 31 after which the position is expected to transfer to onsite at NASA's Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland. At that time permanent telecommuting may be an option for the right candidate but, regardless, the selected candidate must live within reasonable driving distance of Greenbelt to be able to meet in person with customers and colleagues on a routine basis.
Required Qualifications:
BS in Computer Science, Information Systems or web design/development or comparable work experience;
3+ years of experience in deploying commercial or government websites and secure web applications/content management systems;
Critical thinking focused on the delivery of architectures and solutions to challenges;
Sound experience in fundamental web technologies (LAMP, HTML, CSS, Javascript);
Experience using version control systems;
Ability to write maintainable and scalable code;
Excellent team and interpersonal skills. Ability to both take direction and work in a self-directed environment as an effective team member;
An interest in supporting NASA’s communication and research goals.
Desired Qualifications:
Experience developing in an Agile environment;
System/server administration and configuration experience;
Drupal maintenance and development experience;
Working knowledge of Photoshop.

